    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4744" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵνα</span></b> : (1) adv.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">where;</span> this meaning being the primary one, is to be
          assumed in preference to signif. (2), when the sense admits, e. g.
            <i><span class="en">Il. 24.382</span></i>. Apparently
          demonstrative, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">there</span>, in <i><span class="en">Il.
            10.127</span></i>.—(2) conj., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">in order that, that;</span> rarely
          with <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέ</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            12.156</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
